      "id": 1,
      "text": "Miami Shores was officially incorporated in 1932 by Florida legislature, with a landmark at NE 96th St and the bay.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.miamishores.com/history-of-miami-shores/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The village’s first railroad depot, originally named Biscayne, opened in 1932 and helped spur development.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.miamishores.com/history-of-miami-shores/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Brockway Memorial Library, an independent library that opened in 1949 thanks to donor Brockway, remains a cultural hub.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miami_Shores%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The historic Shoreland Company faced bankruptcy in 1927 after a 1926 hurricane, a pivotal moment in the village’s early history.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        17
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.miamishores.com/history-of-miami-shores/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The village’s archives are housed in the Brockway Memorial Library, where visitors can explore local history.",
